Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Lesson 55, from the Earth.\N第55课，来自地球。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.80,0:00:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Greetings.\N问候。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,, astronomy: n.   天文学\N Recent developments in astronomy have made it possible to detect planets in our one milky way and.\N天文学的最新发展使得以我们的银河系方式检测行星成为可能。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.80,0:00:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,, relative: adj. 相对的\N In other galaxies, this is a major achievement because, in relative terms,\N在其他星系中，这是一个重大成就，因为从相对角度来看
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.12,0:00:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,, planets are very small and old knotty-mid light.\N行星非常小，旧的缝合光。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,, Finding planets is proving hard enough,\N寻找行星已经足够困难，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.20,0:00:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,, infinitely: adv. 无限地，无穷地\N but finding life on them will prove infinitely more difficult.\N但是找到自己的生活将变得更加困难。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,, The first question to answer is whether a planet can actually support life.\N要回答的第一个问题是行星是否可以真正支持生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.00,0:00:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,, solar: adj. 太阳系的\N In our one solar system.\N在我们的一个太阳系中。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.24,0:00:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Venus: n.   金星, Mars: n.   火星\N For example, Venus is far too hot and Mars is far too cold to support life.\N例如，金星太热了，火星太冷了，无法支持生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.32,0:00:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,, Only the Earth provides ideal conditions.\N只有地球提供理想的条件。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,, And even here it has taken more than four billion years for plant and animal life to evolve.\N即使在这里，动植物的生命也花费了超过40亿年的发展。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.68,0:00:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,, Whether a planet can support life depends on the size and brightness of its star.\N行星能否支持生命取决于其恒星的大小和亮度。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.12,0:00:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,, That is its Sun.\N那就是它的太阳。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.96,0:00:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,, Imagine a star up T20 times larger.\N想象一下一颗恒星大增加20倍。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.32,0:01:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,, Brighter.\N更明亮。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,, Brighter and hotter than our own Sun.\N比我们自己的阳光更明亮，更热。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.76,0:01:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,, A planet would have to be a very long way from it to be capable of supporting life.\N一个星球必须距离它有很长的路要走才能支持生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.28,0:01:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Alternatively, if the star were small,\N或者，如果恒星很小，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.48,0:01:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,, orbit: n.   运行轨道\N the life-supporting planet would have to have a close orbit round it and also provide the perfect.\N维持生命的星球必须在围绕它的近端围绕轨道，并提供完美的轨道。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.64,0:01:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Conditions for life forms to develop.\N生命形式发展的条件。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.44,0:01:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,, But how would we find such a planet?\N但是，我们如何找到这样的星球呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.92,0:01:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,, At present, there is no telescope in existence that is capable of detecting the presence of life.\N目前，没有望远镜能够检测生命的存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.88,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,, astronomical: adj. 天文学的\N The development of such a telescope will be one of the great astronomical projects of the\N这种望远镜的发展将是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.72,0:01:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,, 21st century.\N21世纪。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.40,0:01:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,, It is impossible to look for life on another planet using Earth-based telescopes.\N使用基于地球的望远镜在另一个星球上寻找生命是不可能的。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.24,0:01:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,, generate: v.   产生\N Our own warm atmosphere and the heat generated by the telescope would make it impossible to detect.\N我们自己的温暖气氛和望远镜产生的热量将使无法检测到。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.80,0:01:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Objects as small as planets.\N像行星一样小的物体。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:01:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,, orbit: n.   运行轨道\N Even a telescope in orbit round the Earth.\N甚至绕地球的轨道上的望远镜。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.24,0:01:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Like the very successful Hubble telescope,\N就像非常成功的哈勃望远镜一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.44,0:02:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,, solar: adj. 太阳系的, particle: n.   微粒，粒子\N would not be suitable because of the dust particles iron solar system.\N由于灰尘颗粒铁太阳系，这将不合适。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Jupiter: n.   木星\N A telescope would have to be as far away as the planet Jupiter to look for life in outer space.\N望远镜必须与木星的行星一样遥远才能在外太空寻找生命。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.80,0:02:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,, solar: adj. 太阳系的\N Because the dust becomes thinner the further we travel towards the outer edges of our own solar.\N因为灰尘变得越来越小，我们越朝着自己的太阳能的外边缘行驶。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.28,0:02:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,, System.\N系统。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,, blot: v.   遮暗\N Once we detected a planet, we would have to find a way of blotting out the light from its star.\N一旦我们发现了一个星球，我们就必须找到一种从其恒星中射出光的方法。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,, So that we would be able to see the planet properly and analyze its atmosphere.\N这样我们就可以正确看到地球并分析其气氛。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,, In the first instance, we would be looking for plant life.\N首先，我们会寻找植物生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.64,0:02:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,, bacteria: n.   细菌\N Rather than little green men, the life forms most likely to develop on a planet would be bacteria.\N最有可能在地球上发展的生命形成而不是小绿色的人，是细菌。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,, generate: v.   产生, bacteria: n.   细菌, oxygen: n.   氧气\N It is bacteria that have generated the oxygen we breathe on Earth.\N是细菌产生了我们在地球上呼吸的氧气。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,, For most of the Earth's history they have been the only form of life on our planet.\N在地球的大部分历史中，它们一直是我们星球上唯一的生活形式。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,, As Earth dwellers, we always cherish the hope that we will be visited by little green men and that we will be able to.\N作为地球居民，我们总是珍惜希望我们将被小绿人拜访，我们将能够拜访。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.04,0:03:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,, realm: n.   领域\N Communicate with them, but this hope is always in the realms of science fiction.\N与他们交流，但这种希望始终是科幻小说的领域。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,, bacteria: n.   细菌\N If we were able to discover lowly forms of life like bacteria on another planet,\N如果我们能够在另一个星球上发现像细菌这样的卑鄙的生活形式，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,, it would completely change our view of ourselves.\N这将完全改变我们对自己的看法。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,, As Daniel Golden of NASA observed, finding life elsewhere would change everything.\N正如美国宇航局的丹尼尔·戈登（Daniel Golden）所观察到的那样，在其他地方找到生活将改变一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,, No human endeavor or thought would be unchanged by it.\N没有人类的努力或思想不会被它改变。
